    "millsfield:images_texts": [
      "FLY\nCALFORNIA CENTRAL,\nCalifarnia\nCalifornia Central Ainlines",
      "Photo taken by A. N. Klaäs,\nsummer, 1953, after flying\nfrom San Francisco to Burbank\nAirport, san Fernando Valley,\nLos Angeles County, California,\nto conclude round-trip B-377\nPan American Airways Cipper trip\nto and from Honolulu, Hawaii.\nM. D. Klaäs collection\nCAL-CENTRAL AIRLINE OFFICIALS CELEBRATE-There are many reasons for the\nbroad smiles worn by Valleyites Colonel C. C. and Mrs. Edna Sherman (center and\nsecond from left) as they meet with advertising officials and press to observe new\nspeedy, luxury Martinliner operation in their intrastate operation. Shown. with this\nman-wife airline combine are (left to right) Arch Keener, company advertising man-\nager; Mildred Fluent of ad agency, Calkins \u0026 Holden, Carlock, McClinon \u0026 Smith,\nand Tom Self. Aviation Week.\nCal-Central Airlines New\nBig Craft Do Record Business\nCalifornia Central Airlines an- geles-San Francisco-Oakland\nrun\nnounced today that its new fleet in less than an hour and a half.\nof five postwar luxury Martinlin-\nThe new Martinliner operation,\ners is\ndoing an all-time record\noperating between four points be-\nbusiness.\ntween\nSan Diego\nand\nthe\nSan\n+ Colonel C. C. Sherman, Cal Cen-\nFrancisco Bay Area, is the latest\ntral president, said that travel via\npublic service on the part of Cali-\nhis airline has soared to unprece-\nfornia Central Airlines,\nthe pio-\ndented levels because of continued\nneer of the West in the field of\naircoach\nfares\non\nthe new 44-\nluxury\nflying at fares\nreduced\nseater,\n300 miles-per-hour\ngiant\none-half against standard flight\nplanes now making\nthe Los An-\nservice.\nCentral Airlines\nBuys New Planes\nCalifornia Central Airlines, Cali-\nfornia's pioneer\nin\nreduced\nfare\ncommutter class intrastate flight\nservices, is partially replacing its\nfleet with five Martin 202s, it is\nreliably reported.\nThe 202s, acquired from North-\nwest Airlines, will have 44 seats,\ntwo lounges and a buffet. Reason\nfor the change from DC-3 service\nis\ngreater\nspeed,\ncomfort and\nheavier\ndensity loads\nto\nmeet\ngrowing travel demands, it is fur-\nther understood.\nNo starting date for the\nnew\nMICHAEL\nservice has been announced.\nMICHAEL\nMICHAEL\nKLA AS.\nKLA AS\n208.112,0\nOT C"
    ],
